that I maximize the reward.

733
00:28:20,230 --> 00:28:22,150
So I'll have to define
a reward, right.

734
00:28:22,150 --> 00:28:25,410
Maybe a reward is a number of
pieces of opponent's pieces

735
00:28:25,410 --> 00:28:26,830
I've knocked off the board.

736
00:28:26,830 --> 00:28:29,440
Or maybe reward is
just win the game.

737
00:28:29,440 --> 00:28:30,232
Don't win the game.

738
00:28:30,232 --> 00:28:32,107
And so I'll just make
a bunch of random moves

739
00:28:32,107 --> 00:28:33,827
until I get to the
very end of the game.

740
00:28:33,827 --> 00:28:35,410
And that's actually
how they did this.

741
00:28:35,410 --> 00:28:36,060
That's how they trained this.

742
00:28:36,060 --> 00:28:37,800
Is they said, OK,
well, let's just

743
00:28:37,800 --> 00:28:41,430
let two reinforcement learning
agents play against each other,

744
00:28:41,430 --> 00:28:44,820
make random moves, and then,
eventually, one of them

745
00:28:44,820 --> 00:28:47,130
will win, meaning that
some move in there,

746
00:28:47,130 --> 00:28:48,870
some set of moves
in there was better

747
00:28:48,870 --> 00:28:50,470
than what the other one did.

748
00:28:50,470 --> 00:28:51,820
And let's learn from that.

749
00:28:51,820 --> 00:28:54,340
I've now created labeled
data to some extent, right.

750
00:28:54,340 --> 00:28:58,440
The state, the
observation about my space

751
00:28:58,440 --> 00:29:03,530
is the input x and the
output is the action.

752
00:29:03,530 --> 00:29:05,590
Given the input,
state of the board,

753
00:29:05,590 --> 00:29:07,820
predict the next
best action to take.

754
00:29:07,820 --> 00:29:10,360
And the loss
function here is now

755
00:29:10,360 --> 00:29:12,680
trying to actually maximize
the reward function.

756
00:29:12,680 --> 00:29:14,350
So as opposed to
minimizing the loss,

757
00:29:14,350 --> 00:29:16,120
I'm trying to
maximize the reward.

758
00:29:16,120 --> 00:29:17,890
Similar idea though.

759
00:29:17,890 --> 00:29:20,530
This same idea persists
and is used a lot

760
00:29:20,530 --> 00:29:22,440
in training self-driving cars.

761
00:29:22,440 --> 00:29:25,040
Is I can observe the
state of my world, right.

762
00:29:25,040 --> 00:29:27,005
I can collect all the
data from every sensor

763
00:29:27,005 --> 00:29:28,630
that I have in my
car, all the cameras,

764
00:29:28,630 --> 00:29:30,880
lidar, radar, whatever it is.

765
00:29:30,880 --> 00:29:33,520
I can feed that into my
reinforcement learning agent,

766
00:29:33,520 --> 00:29:34,850
which is just a neural network.

767
00:29:34,850 --> 00:29:37,970
And the way we've implemented
them in the modern era.

768
00:29:37,970 --> 00:29:40,390
So I feed all of
those sensors as input

769
00:29:40,390 --> 00:29:42,880
to my reinforcement learning
agent, to my neural network,

770
00:29:42,880 --> 00:29:44,860
and I predict the next
best action, right?

771
00:29:44,860 --> 00:29:46,090
Steer left, steer right.

772
00:29:46,090 --> 00:29:48,670
How much to steer left,
how much to steer right,

773
00:29:48,670 --> 00:29:50,000
accelerate, brake.

774
00:29:50,000 --> 00:29:52,010
That's all part of
my action space.

775
00:29:52,010 --> 00:29:54,530
So I decide the next
best action to take

776
00:29:54,530 --> 00:29:55,970
and then I evaluate that.

777
00:29:55,970 --> 00:29:58,880
I take that action and I see
how good that action was.

778
00:29:58,880 --> 00:30:00,762
And if it got me closer
to my destination

779
00:30:00,762 --> 00:30:02,470
or didn't result in
an accident, however,

780
00:30:02,470 --> 00:30:06,070
I define my reward
function that will be

781
00:30:06,070 --> 00:30:09,860
or that will be, kind of,
what I try to maximize, right.

782
00:30:09,860 --> 00:30:12,500
I'm going to try to maximize
that reward function.

783
00:30:12,500 --> 00:30:14,602
And that's a
non-trivial task also.

784
00:30:14,602 --> 00:30:16,060
So I'm not going
to pretend that is

785
00:30:16,060 --> 00:30:18,520
an easy thing by any means,
because, for example, let's

786
00:30:18,520 --> 00:30:20,150
take the self-driving car case.

787
00:30:20,150 --> 00:30:24,820
If I define my reward function
as getting to my destination,

788
00:30:24,820 --> 00:30:26,920
well then it's likely
going to just break

789
00:30:26,920 --> 00:30:30,160
every rule of the road to just
maximize the reward of getting

790
00:30:30,160 --> 00:30:31,150
to the destination.

791
00:30:31,150 --> 00:30:34,480
Or potentially, I don't
know what's worse,

792
00:30:34,480 --> 00:30:36,910
it'll do the opposite
and just say, well, I'll

793
00:30:36,910 --> 00:30:39,970
drive 1 miles per hour
because at least then I

794
00:30:39,970 --> 00:30:43,150
don't crash into things
and so I will eventually

795
00:30:43,150 --> 00:30:44,660
make it to my destination.

796
00:30:44,660 --> 00:30:47,650
So maybe I say, OK, I'll
penalize you for every second

797
00:30:47,650 --> 00:30:50,030
that you're not at
the destination.

798
00:30:50,030 --> 00:30:52,060
Well, then it will
learn to go faster,

799
00:30:52,060 --> 00:30:55,000
but it'll likely go too fast and
again, break every rule of road,

800
00:30:55,000 --> 00:30:56,518
crash into things and just race.

801
00:30:56,518 --> 00:30:58,060
And it'll find some
balance, probably

802
00:30:58,060 --> 00:31:01,070
between crashing into things
and getting to the destination

803
00:31:01,070 --> 00:31:04,250
but it'll likely be a huge
risk and a huge liability.

804
00:31:04,250 --> 00:31:07,060
And so this question of how
to actually optimize this

805
00:31:07,060 --> 00:31:08,560
or how to define
the reward function

806
00:31:08,560 --> 00:31:11,080
such that the reinforcement
learning agent, the neural net

807
00:31:11,080 --> 00:31:13,030
doesn't find some
sort of shortcut,

808
00:31:13,030 --> 00:31:15,530
that is a really, really
hard research question.

809
00:31:15,530 --> 00:31:18,320
And they talk about this again
a bit in this documentary.

